body:
I have a  lag at the first time when animation loading on the screen (in android emulator is much more noticeable)
I tried to use 

```
 lifecycleScope.launch {
            withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {
               suspendCoroutine<Unit> { c ->
                    LottieCompositionFactory.fromRawRes(requireContext(), R.raw.lottie_animation).addListener {
                      c.resume(Unit)
                    }
                }
            }
       // Launch my fragment here where composable playing animation of R.raw.lottie_animation
}
```
In  a fragment composable widget responsible for lottie animation looks like this:
```
@Composable
fun lottie() {
   val composition by rememberLottieComposition(LottieCompositionSpec.RawRes(R.raw.lottie_animation))
   val progress by animateLottieCompositionAsState(composition,
                  clipSpec = LottieClipSpec.Progress(prgs.first, prgs.second)
          )
   LottieAnimation(modifier = Modifier.fillMaxWidth(), composition = composition, progress = progress)
}
```

But I still see the lag :( regardless I'm using LottieCompositionFactory.fromRawRes or not. Do you know why is not helping to preload lottie animation and eliminate first loading/initialisation animation lag?

The version I use 
4.1.0 (lottie-compose artifact)


**What version of Android did you test this on?**
Android 10 and 11

**Steps To Reproduce**
Just try code I described above use heavy lottie json to observe lag more clearly (especially if you try on Android emulator or old low performing Android phone)
